    "causal_summary": "Five keystone consumers converge on one shared core that does not exist yet (`research.md` section 4). Three are write-time front doors with a safe-apply path: A1 is on-write and report-only, B1 is scheduled and headless, B2 is interactive on `/doctor`. The other two register on the engine without a safe-apply path. B3 emits queue rows. Every Tier-C retrieval detector must pass one promotion gate. SC-001 measures the three write-time front doors A1, B1, B2. With no shared core each front door would carry its own detector list, its own notion of what a safe fix is, and its own write path, so the five would drift on the one decision that matters: whether a given fix is allowed to mutate a git-tracked authored artifact. There is no `detector-registry.ts` single source of truth and no `dq-engine.ts` pure runner today, so the deny-by-default safety property the program depends on has nowhere to live.",
